          <h1 style="color:#004C45;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;margin:0;text-align: left;"> A Message from Cal Poly Humboldt </h1>
          <p id="date" style="color:#004C45;font-size:14px;font-weight:bold;margin:10px 0 20px 0;text-align: left;"> November 17, 2023 </p>
          <p style="color:#004C45;font-size:22px;font-weight:bold;margin:10px 0 20px 0; line-height:28px"> Informal Time Off for Fall Break </p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-divider border-color="#F2A900" padding="0" />
      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
    <mj-section css-class="light-wrap" padding-bottom="20px">
      <mj-column>
        <mj-text>Dear colleagues:
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text>I sincerely appreciate each of you for all you've done this Fall semester. As always, you have continued to further Cal Poly Humboldtâ€™s goal of providing a positive, meaningful educational experience for our students. Also, thank you to everyone who has engaged in the planning of our many University initiatives.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>In gratitude, I am authorizing staff to end their work three hours prior to the end of their workday on Wednesday, November 22, 2023. To ensure that necessary work is completed, appropriate administrators must approve this paid Informal Time Off (ITO).
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text>Pay instructions:</mj-text>
        <mj-text>If you take vacation on Wednesday, November 22, 2023, record eight (8) hours of vacation in PeopleSoft and take three (3) hours of ITO at a later date. If you work your full shift on Wednesday, take three (3) hours of ITO at a later date. ITO is not recorded in PeopleSoft and must be taken prior to June 30, 2024 with the approval of your appropriate administrator.</mj-text>
        <mj-text>Thank you for all your contributions to our campus. Please have a safe and restful fall break!</mj-text>
        <mj-text>
          With best wishes, <br>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-image width="175px" align="left" src="https://mailings.humboldt.edu/general/signatures/presidentJackson_officialSignature.png" alt="Tom Jackson, Jr." />
         <mj-text>
           Tom Jackson, Jr., President <br>
           Cal Poly Humboldt</mj-text>

      </mj-column>
    </mj-section>
